Headline: Zoom updates its terms to let the company train its AI models using some customer data, and says it doesn't use audio, video, or chat content without consent
OpenAI details GPTBot, which the company uses to crawl the web for data to improve its AI models, and how site admins can opt out using robots.txt
Developer logs: Apple is testing an M3 Max chip with a 16-core CPU, a 40-core GPU, and 48GB of RAM, in a MacBook Pro that's expected to debut in 2024
Zoom, known for helping millions of people work from home, asks its employees living within 50 miles of an office to work in person at least two days per week
PayPal debuts PYUSD, a Paxos-issued stablecoin and fully backed by USD deposits, short-term Treasuries, and cash equivalents, rolling out to US users gradually
Microsoft says Bing Chat, which is only available in products like its Edge browser and Bing app, is coming “soon” to third-party browsers, including on mobile
Sources: Apple has a deal where TSMC effectively eats the cost of chip defects, saving billions for Apple, which will get 3nm chips about a year before rivals
Sources: in late 2020, the NSA discovered that Chinese hackers had access to Japanese defense networks, with the problem persisting until at least fall 2021
How a false facial recognition match led to Detroit police wrongfully arresting a Black woman for carjacking and robbery, the first such known case for a woman
Austin-based One Model, which uses AI to help employers make recruiting, hiring, layoffs, and other HR decisions, raised $41M led by Riverwood Capital
Sources: Meta disbanded the team behind its protein-folding AI project ESMFold this spring, prioritizing commercial AI products over blue-sky research
A US judge denies Google a summary judgment in a $5B lawsuit over the way it tracked users' internet activities in Incognito mode, pushing it closer to a trial
The European Commission opens an in-depth probe into Adobe's $20B Figma deal, after a preliminary review triggered concerns that it may reduce competition
Neuralink, the brain-computer interface startup Elon Musk co-founded, raised a $280M Series D led by Founders Fund, after a reported ~$5B valuation in June 2023
China releases draft rules for limiting the use of facial recognition to “specific purposes and full necessity,” requiring individual approval, and more
Researchers tested 14 LLMs for political bias and found OpenAI's GPT-4 was the most left-wing libertarian and Meta's LLaMA was the most right-wing authoritarian
Atlanta-based Tractian, which uses AI and edge computing to identify industrial machine failures, raised a $45M Series B led by General Catalyst
Researchers: North Korean hackers placed backdoors at Russian rocket design bureau NPO Mashinostroyeniya for at least five months in 2022 to see emails and more
